<h3>The Substantive vs. Cosmetic Test</h3>
<p>The FTC applies a substantive versus cosmetic test. If the AI use materially affects how consumers interpret the content, disclosure is required. If the AI use is purely cosmetic and does not affect interpretation, disclosure is not required.</p>
<p>For example, using AI to smooth skin in a beauty product ad may be cosmetic. Using AI to generate a before-and-after image showing results the product cannot actually achieve is substantive and deceptive.</p>
